---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Contact | severancepayestimator.com"
  description="Contact the SeveranceCalc editorial team with questions, corrections, or partnership inquiries."
>
  <h1>Contact</h1>

  <p>
    We welcome questions, corrections, and feedback. If you've spotted an error in our content or have a suggestion for a new guide topic, please get in touch.
  </p>

  <div class="card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0;">General Inquiries</h2>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a></p>
    <p>We aim to respond within 2 business days.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What We Can Help With</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Content corrections:</strong> If you believe something on this site contains a factual error, please describe the issue and include the URL of the affected page.</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial suggestions:</strong> We're always looking for topics our readers need covered. If there's a severance or separation issue we haven't addressed, let us know.</li>
    <li><strong>Media and partnership inquiries:</strong> For media requests or partnership discussions, please use the general email above with "Media" or "Partnership" in the subject line.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What We Cannot Help With</h2>
  <p>
    We are not a law firm and cannot provide legal advice about your specific situation. If you have received a severance offer and need guidance, please consult a licensed employment attorney in your state. Many employment attorneys offer free or low-cost initial consultations for severance review matters.
  </p>
  <p>
    For general information about severance calculation, types of packages, and the review process, please explore our <a href="/guides">guides</a> and <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
